cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.ROB

This paper involves the use of deep learning to generate vasculature maps from structural OCT images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of AI to bypass the need for expert labeling also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The application of this technology to medical imaging and the use of OCTA and motion artifacts suggest a potential fit for the medical imaging (cs.MED) and robotics (cs.ROB) sub-categories.
